ODM party leader Raila Odinga will today take his campaigns to Narok county ahead of the August elections. Raila who has been selling his Azimio la Umoja agenda, is expected to have a rally at Ololulunga at 11am. He will later on address another rally at Ewaso Ngiro at around 2pm. Raila, DP William Rutoâ€™s main challenger in the State House race, has promised to introduce the social welfare programmes to help poor households put food on the table if elected president in the August 9 polls. On the other hand, DP William Ruto is expected in Makueni county later today. Ruto will start off by attending Kathonzweni AIC Church in Kathonzweni town at around 9am. Thereafter, the DP will then set out to Nzeveni Market where he will stage a rally from 11am onwards before proceeding to Nguumo at 2pm. Ruto is expected to market his bottom-up economic model. HE said his administration will BE carrying on with the development started by the current government.